problem:
Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$.

response:
 When <var>c</var> = 3, the expression \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} becomes \begin{align*}
\left(3^3-3(3-1)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}. Simplifying further, we get \begin{align*}
\left(27-3(2)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}, which simplifies to \begin{align*}
\left(27-24\right)^3
\end{align*}, and finally to \begin{align*}
3^3
\end{align*}. </think> <answer> $3^3$ </answer>

