Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$.

response:
 When $c=3$, we can evaluate the expression \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} by substituting $c=3$ and simplifying the expression. First, let's simplify inside the parentheses: \begin{align*}
c^c &= 3^3 = 27, \\
c(c-1)^c &= 3(2)^3 = 3*8 = 24.
\end{align*} Then, subtracting these two values, we get \begin{align*}
27-24 = 3.
\end{align*} Now, raising this result to the power of $c$, we have \begin{align*}
\left(3\right)^3 = 27.
\end{align*} <answer> 27 </answer>

problem:
Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$.

response:
 When $c = 3$, the expression inside the parentheses becomes \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c = \left(3^3-3(3-1)^3\right)^3 = \left(27-3\cdot2^3\right)^3 = \left(27-24\right)^3 = 3^3 = 27.
\end{align*} So the answer is $\boxed{27}$. </think> <answer> $27$ </answer>

